Format data

ClusterProfiler vignette Because of poor dog annotations we use homolog genes from human for KEGG/disease/GO analysis

# Restore the object
hsa.map  <- readRDS(file = "hsa.map.rds2")
# filter out the NA genes from LRT test (low counts or outliers)
hsa.map <- subset(hsa.map, !is.na(LRT_padj))
hsa.map$lfg_CTLvsATPlog2FoldChange[is.na(hsa.map$lfg_CTLvsATPlog2FoldChange)] <- 0
hsa.map$lfg_CTLvsAVB.log2FoldChange[is.na(hsa.map$lfg_CTLvsAVB.log2FoldChange)] <- 0
hsa.map$lfg_AVBvsATPlog2FoldChange[is.na(hsa.map$lfg_AVBvsATPlog2FoldChange)] <- 0

How many genes are lost from getting human homologs?

CTLvsATP_lfc1 <- subset(hsa.map, abs(lfg_CTLvsATPlog2FoldChange) >1 , select=c(entrezgene_id, lfg_CTLvsATPlog2FoldChange, ensembl_gene_id))

cat("unique dog genes in lfg_CTLvsATP >1: ", length(unique(CTLvsATP_lfc1$ensembl_gene_id)), "\nunique mapped human genes in lfg_CTLvsATP >1: ", length(unique(CTLvsATP_lfc1$entrezgene_id)))

To be parsed in clusterprofiler as long character

CTLvsATP <- subset(hsa.map, select=c(entrezgene_id, lfg_CTLvsATPlog2FoldChange))
CTLvsATP <- CTLvsATP[order(-CTLvsATP$lfg_CTLvsATPlog2FoldChange),]

#making list of doubles for DE pathways/diseases/KEGG functions
t.CTLvsATP <- t(CTLvsATP)
colnames(t.CTLvsATP) <- t.CTLvsATP[1,]
t.CTLvsATP <- t.CTLvsATP[2,]

l.CTLvsATP <- list(t.CTLvsATP)
l.CTLvsATP <- unlist(l.CTLvsATP)


#same for other contrasts
CTLvsAVB <- subset(hsa.map, select=c(entrezgene_id, lfg_CTLvsAVB.log2FoldChange))
AVBvsATP <- subset(hsa.map, select=c(entrezgene_id, lfg_AVBvsATPlog2FoldChange))

CTLvsAVB <- CTLvsAVB[order(-CTLvsAVB$lfg_CTLvsAVB.log2FoldChange),]
AVBvsATP <- AVBvsATP[order(-AVBvsATP$lfg_AVBvsATPlog2FoldChange),]

t.CTLvsAVB <- t(CTLvsAVB)
t.AVBvsATP <- t(AVBvsATP)
colnames(t.CTLvsAVB) <- t.CTLvsAVB[1,]
colnames(t.AVBvsATP) <- t.AVBvsATP[1,]
t.CTLvsAVB <- t.CTLvsAVB[2,]
t.AVBvsATP <- t.AVBvsATP[2,]

l.CTLvsAVB <- list(t.CTLvsAVB)
l.AVBvsATP <- list(t.AVBvsATP)

l.CTLvsAVB <- unlist(l.CTLvsAVB)
l.AVBvsATP <- unlist(l.AVBvsATP)



de_CTLvsATP <- names(l.CTLvsATP)[abs(l.CTLvsATP) > 1]
de_CTLvsATP <- de_CTLvsATP[!is.na(de_CTLvsATP)]

de_CTLvsAVB <- names(l.CTLvsAVB)[abs(l.CTLvsAVB) > 1]
de_CTLvsAVB <- de_CTLvsAVB[!is.na(de_CTLvsAVB)]

de_AVBvsATP <- names(l.AVBvsATP)[abs(l.AVBvsATP) > 1]
de_AVBvsATP <- de_AVBvsATP[!is.na(de_AVBvsATP)]
